summary:
This study pays particular attention to Malay-Indonesian manuscripts which has not been examined
[precisely] so far. The manuscripts examined in this article are kept in the Leiden University Library
whose content or origin remained under-researched. In some instances, the manuscripts have not been
comprehensively examined. The following themes are analysed: 

1. Persian Musical Modes and Poems in the Malay-Indonesian world;
Persian Rhythmic Poems Copied by Malays; 
Rhythmic Mystical Supplication to ʿAlī b. Abī Ṭālib;
Poems of Lal Shahbaz Qalandar;
2. Familiarity with the Persian Language
3.Learning Islamic Sciences through Persian
4. Persianized Malay and Malayized Persian
